38:  * This filter is used to make explicit decision on which nodes certain shard
39:  * can / should be allocated. The decision if a shard can be allocated, must not
40:  * be allocated or should be allocated is based on either cluster wide dynamic
41:  * settings ({@code cluster.routing.allocation.*}) or index specific dynamic
42:  * settings ({@code index.routing.allocation.*}). All of those settings can be
43:  * changed at runtime via the cluster or the index update settings API.
44:  * </p>
45:  * Note: Cluster settings are applied first and will override index specific
46:  * settings such that if a shard can be allocated according to the index routing
47:  * settings it wont be allocated on a node if the cluster specific settings
48:  * would disallow the allocation. Filters are applied in the following order:
